# Stage 0: Project structure

Build-system-owned config, discovery and source preparation.

## Contract

- Input: project input file or directory and builder metadata
- Output: module inputs, parsed `config.bst`, prepared source-library roots, one source-tree index, discovered source assets and string-table base
- Decides: config keys, module-root discovery, source kinds, external provider resolution
- Must not decide: semantic compilation, HIR shape, borrow validation
- Invariant: config compilation stops at AST because config produces no runtime code
- Invariant: directory builds perform one expensive source-tree indexing pass after config establishes discovery roots

## Main paths

- `src/build_system/create_project_modules/`
- `src/build_system/project_config.rs`
- `src/build_system/project_config/`

